Actually, it’s correct as “Also, shouldn’t your sentence asking if his sentence should end in a period end in a question mark?”
I was describing the sentence, not what it was doing. I was talking about haticks’s sentence that was asking if Mopman’s sentence should in a period, not asking if his sentence should be asking.
It could be revised as “Also, shouldn’t your sentence that was asking if his sentence should end in a period end in a question mark?”, but they’re both acceptable.
